{
  "texts": [
    "2.4.Comparison with other models.",
    "The model that we have introduced takes inspiration from the one in [26] and can be seen as its kinetic counterpart.",
    "The most relevant difference consists in the way microscopic variations (2) of the opinion work.",
    "Indeed, in [26] the probability that an agent interacts with another solely depends on the activity level of the former, but when the interaction takes place both agents are influenced.",
    "Therefore, in order to reproduce the original model with a kinetic approach, we should consider interactions of the form⎧ ⎪ ⎪ ⎨ ⎪ ⎪ ⎩ w ′ = w + Ãw,p G(w, v)λ p (v -w) + Ãv,p G(w, v)λ p (v -w) + D(w)η p, v ′ = v + Ãw,p G(v, w)λ p (w -v) + Ãv,p G(v, w)λ p (w -v) + D(v)η p,where the discrete random variables Ãw,p and Ãv,p are related to the activity levels of the first and second agent, respectively."
  ]
}